text: Bay 22nd Street, east side, between Cropsey Ave. (left) and Warehouse Ave., showing a group of frame houses once used as a summer house at Gravesend Beach. At the left is a modern apartment No.1926-28 Cropsey Ave. [Date] April 27, 1935.

Bay 22nd Street, east side, between Cropsey Ave. (left) and Warehouse Ave., showing a group of frame houses once used as a summer house at Gravesend Beach. At the left is a modern apartment No.1926-28 Cropsey Ave. [Date] April 27, 1935.

Bay 22nd Street, east side, between Cropsey Ave. (left) and Warehouse Ave., showing a group of frame houses once used as a summer house at Gravesend Beach. At the left is a modern apartment No.1926-28 Cropsey Ave. [Date] April 27, 1935.

Gravesend Bay, at the foot of 21st Ave., showing a break water encircling a portion of the Bay, that will eventually be filled in and have Warehouse Ave., extended thereon. View 1, shows homes numbered 1916-1962 on Cropsey Ave. at the present shore line. Shortly they will be two blocks inland. Nos. 2 and 3 are westward and show the encircling stone barrier.

April 27, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
